    "Name": "Mithras Light Tank",
    "Details": "The Mithras Light Tank is a combat vehicle that was originally intended to be a scout in addition to its place on the battlefield as a swift, light tank that is capable at all ranges. Capable of speeds up to 97 km/h, the Mithras can keep up with most units, while still providing respectable firepower with decent armor. Though that protection is only three tons worth, it is improved through the use of Ferro-Fibrous. For use at long range, the Mithras has a Ultra Autocannon/2 mounted in a turret. Two ER Medium Lasers provide additional firepower at short range in case an enemy makes it in under the minimum range of the autocannon.\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Tracked: High traction, agile turning.</color></b>\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n <b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 6/9 Hex: 180/270 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<b>Armor:</b> Ferro-Fibrous (C)\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>        85     15\n<b>Left</b>          60     15\n<b>Right</b>        60     15\n<b>Rear</b>         50     15\n<b>Turret</b>       60     15\n\n<b>Total</b>      315     75\n",
